The paper deals with network coding and network alignment in acyclic networks with delay, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of finite-field discrete Fourier transform (DFT) suggests a signal processing aspect, which falls under cs.SI. The paper also proposes Precoding Based Network Alignment (PBNA) schemes, which involve optimization and coding techniques, falling under cs.DC and cs.CC respectively.
